CPANPLUS-Dist-Slackware version 0.02

This CPANPLUS plugin creates Slackware compatible packages from Perl
distributions.

    $ cpanp
    CPAN Terminal> i Some::Module --format=CPANPLUS::Dist::Slackware

    $ cpan2dist --format CPANPLUS::Dist::Slackware Some::Module

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

DEPENDENCIES

The Slackware Linux package management tools and the sudo command are
required.  The fakeroot command is highly recommended.  You can download a
script that builds fakeroot from http://slackbuilds.org/.

Perl 5.10 provides all required Perl modules.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc CPANPLUS::Dist::Slackware

If you want to hack on the source it might be a good idea to grab the
latest version with git using the command:

    git clone git://github.com/voegelas/CPANPLUS-Dist-Slackware.git

